M|nodes-overview|name: pletor-node-basics
M|nodes-overview|description: >-
M|nodes-overview|Core knw for building Pletor workflows. Use this skill whenever the user wants to create, design, or describe a Pletor workflow — even partially. Covers node categories, how nodes connect, data flow, 
M|nodes-overview|version: 1.0.0
M|nodes-overview|platforms: []
M|nodes-overview|metadata:
M|nodes-overview|hermes:
M|nodes-overview|tags: [coo, operations, workflow, planning, sprint, milestones, process, automation]
M|nodes-overview|Pletor is a no-code workflow builder for AI-powered visual mkt. Workflows are built
M|nodes-overview|by connecting **nodes** on a canvas. Data flows **left → right** from inputs through
M|nodes-overview|processing to outputs.
M|nodes-overview|These nodes feed information into the workflow. They have no AI processing.
M|nodes-overview|| Node | What it does |
M|nodes-overview||------|-------------|
M|nodes-overview|| **Text Prompt** | User-typed instruction (the creative brief) |
M|nodes-overview|| **Upload Image** | Static or user-uploaded image reference |
M|nodes-overview|| **Upload Video / Audio / File** | Other media or doc inputs |
M|nodes-overview|| **Brand ctx** | Company name, positioning, audience |
M|nodes-overview|| **Visual References** | Reference images that anchor the visual style |
M|nodes-overview|| **Brand Guidelines** | Creative do's/don'ts, colors, layout rules |
M|nodes-overview|| **Brand Voice** | Writing samples and tone-of-voice examples |
M|nodes-overview|| **Brand Docs** | Full brand books as PDF/CSV/JSON/TXT |
M|nodes-overview|> **Best practice:** Always add Brand ctx + Visual References for brand-safe output.
M|nodes-overview|> Layer multiple brand nodes — each adds a different dimension of consistency.
M|nodes-overview|These nodes run AI models. They are the creative engines.
M|nodes-overview|| Node | What it does |
M|nodes-overview||------|-------------|
M|nodes-overview|| **gen Image** | Text-to-image or image-to-image |
M|nodes-overview|| **Edit Image** | Modify an existing image with text instructions |
M|nodes-overview|| **gen Video** | Text-to-video or image-to-video |
M|nodes-overview|| **gen Lipsync** | Animate a portrait/video character to speak audio |
M|nodes-overview|| **gen Audio** | Voice or sound design generation |
M|nodes-overview|| **Text Assistant** | Pre-built LLM expert (prompt enhancer, copy writer, analyzer) |
M|nodes-overview|| **gen Text** | Raw LLM with custom instructions |
M|nodes-overview|| **Upscale Image / Video** | Resolution enhancement post-generation |
M|nodes-overview|| **Remove Background** | Strip image/video background to transparent |
M|nodes-overview|| **Edit Video** | Modify video cnt with text instructions |
M|nodes-overview|| **Extract Video Frame** | Pull a still frame from video (useful as image input) |
M|nodes-overview|These nodes control flow, combine data, and connect to external services.
M|nodes-overview|| Node | What it does |
M|nodes-overview||------|-------------|
M|nodes-overview|| **Composer** | Layer images, text, logos into a final composed visual or video |
M|nodes-overview|| **Prompt Concatenator** | Mechanically join multiple text inputs into one prompt |
M|nodes-overview|| **Split Text** | Break text into parts by delimiter |
M|nodes-overview|| **List Selector** | Pick one item from a list by index |
M|nodes-overview|| **Human rv** | Pause workflow for manual ap before continuing |
M|nodes-overview|| **Router** | Reuse one node's output in multiple downstream nodes |
M|nodes-overview|| **Rename Asset** | Set custom filenames (supports dynamic naming patterns) |
M|nodes-overview|| **Merge Videos** | Combine multiple video clips into one |
M|nodes-overview|| **Google Drive** | Pull assets in or push outputs out |
M|nodes-overview|| **Meta / TikTok / Instagram** | Publish directly to ad platforms |
M|nodes-overview|**Always put a Text Assistant between user input and generation nodes.**
M|nodes-overview|Raw user prompts are rarely optimal for AI models. A Text Assistant enhances, combines,
M|nodes-overview|and structures the prompt before it reaches the generator — this dramatically improves
M|nodes-overview|output quality and consistency.
M|nodes-overview|**Pattern 1 — Simple Generation**
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|Text Prompt → [Text Assistant: Enhance Prompt] → gen Image → Upscale Image
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|**Pattern 2 — Brand-safe Image**
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|Text Prompt ───┐
M|nodes-overview|Brand ctx ─┼─ Text Assistant → gen Image
M|nodes-overview|Visual Refs ───┘
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|**Pattern 3 — Image-to-Video (recommended over text-to-video)**
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|Upload Image → [Text Assistant] → gen Image → gen Video
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|gen a still image first for far more control over the final video.
M|nodes-overview|**Pattern 4 — Product Shot with Custom Background**
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|Upload Image → gen Image → Remove Background → Composer
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|**Pattern 5 — Ad Creative with Localization**
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|Text Prompt ───┐
M|nodes-overview|Brand Nodes ───┼─ Text Assistant → gen Image → Composer
M|nodes-overview|Logo Upload ───┘
M|nodes-overview|→ Localization Text Assistant ───→ Text Prompt (language)
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|**Pattern 6 — Lipsync Talking Character**
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|Upload Image/Video → gen Lipsync (+ audio input or text-to-speech)
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|When writing instructions for **Text Assistant** or **gen Text** nodes, structure prompts clearly:
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|[Subject/Character] → [Action/Pose] → [Setting/Background] → [Style/Mood] →
M|nodes-overview|[Lighting] → [Camera/Composition] → [Brand/Color cues]
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|Example:
M|nodes-overview|> "A confident woman in her 30s holding a coffee cup, seated in a modern co-working
M|nodes-overview|> space, warm natural light from the left, editorial lifestyle photography,
M|nodes-overview|> Leica 35mm aesthetic, brand palette: off-white and forest green"
M|nodes-overview|Be explicit about:
M|nodes-overview|1. **Role**: "You are a creative director specializing in luxury brand photography."
M|nodes-overview|2. **Task**: "Enhance the user's raw prompt into a detailed image generation prompt."
M|nodes-overview|3. **Format**: "Return only the final prompt, no explanation."
M|nodes-overview|4. **Constraints**: "Always include the brand color palette: [colors]. Never include human faces."
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|[Subject] → [Motion/Action description] → [Camera movement] → [Duration/Pace] → [Style]
M|nodes-overview|```
M|nodes-overview|Key: describe motion explicitly. Video models respond to verbs.
M|nodes-overview|Example:
M|nodes-overview|> "A bottle of perfume rotating slowly on a marble surface, camera gently pushes in,
M|nodes-overview|> soft diffused studio lighting, cinematic, 5-second loop"
M|nodes-overview|Choose one of two strategies:
M|nodes-overview|- **Input-led**: Start with what you have (product image, brief) → add transformation nodes forward
M|nodes-overview|- **Output-led**: Start with the desired output (Instagram ad) → pick the right AI node → work backwards to define inputs
M|nodes-overview|Start simple (2–3 nodes), test, then add complexity. Test individual nodes in isolation before running the full chain.
M|nodes-overview|When describing a workflow to a user, always output:
M|nodes-overview|1. **Goal**: one sentence describing what the workflow produces
M|nodes-overview|2. **Node Chain**: step-by-step list with node type and its role
M|nodes-overview|3. **Key cfg Notes**: any critical settings, model choices, or prompt tips
M|nodes-overview|4. **Optional Enhancements**: nodes to add for more power (brand nodes, human rv, etc.)
M|nodes-overview|See `skills/workflow/model-selection/SKILL.md` (Atlas) for model choices, and `skills/workflow/advanced-nodes/SKILL.md` (Pixel) for Composer, Logic nodes, and integration nodes in depth.